==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*apala-'', from Indo-European ''*abl-, *ablu-''.  Cognate with Old Frisian ''[[appel]]'', Old Saxon ''[[appel]]'' (Dutch ''[[appel]]''), Old High German ''[[apful]]'' (German ''[[Apfel]]''), Old Norse ''[[epli]]'' (Swedish ''[[äpple]]''), Crimean Gothic [[𐌰𐍀𐌴𐌻]].  The IE root is also the source of Old Irish ''[[ubull]]'' (Irish ''[[úll]]''), Lithuanian ''[[obuolys]]'', Common Slavonic ''jabl’ko'' (Russian ''[[яблоко]]'').

